1ï¸âƒ£ Move website files to web root

Default NGINX web root:
sudo cp -r Charity-Trust /var/www/html/

Final path should be:
/var/www/html/Charity-Trust/index.html


2ï¸âƒ£ Create NGINX server block (virtual host)

Create config file:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/charity-trust


Paste this:
nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;

    root /var/www/html/Charity-Trust;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}

Save and exit.

3ï¸âƒ£ Enable the site
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/charity-trust /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/


4ï¸âƒ£ Remove default config (important)
sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default

5ï¸âƒ£ Test NGINX config
sudo nginx -t

If output is:
syntax is ok
test is successful

Proceed.

6ï¸âƒ£ Reload NGINX
sudo systemctl reload nginx


Open browser
http://SERVER-IP
sudo systemctl status nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx


ðŸ”¥ Firewall blocking port 80

sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw reload


For AWS EC2:
Open **port 80** in **Security Group**
ðŸ”¥ No index.html

Check:
ls /var/www/html/Charity-Trust
Must contain:
index.html

## Quick test (very useful)
Test locally:
curl http://localhost

## Interview tip (important)

> NGINX serves files from **/var/www/html**, not from **/etc/nginx**.


